```

Now HTML fields in list views will have a much more compact minimum height of 15px instead of 60px. This will make the list views less bloated while still displaying the content properly.

Fixed! I've replaced the `numbering` attribute with CSS-based row numbering which is more reliable:

## Changes Made:

### **Added CSS for Row Numbers:**
```css
/* Add row numbers to activities list */
.o_list_table.o_list_table_numbered {
    counter-reset: row-num;
}
.o_list_table.o_list_table_numbered tbody tr {
    counter-increment: row-num;
}
.o_list_table.o_list_table_numbered tbody tr td:first-child::before {
    content: counter(row-num) ". ";
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #6c757d;
    margin-right: 5px;
}
```

### **Updated List Classes:**
```xml
<!-- Before -->
class="o_list_view_compact" numbering="1"

<!-- After -->
class="o_list_view_compact o_list_table_numbered"
```

## How It Works:

- Uses CSS counters (counter-reset, counter-increment)
- Adds "1. ", "2. ", "3. " etc. before the first column
- Numbers are **bold** and **gray** for visibility
- Works in both "Planned" and "Done" sections

**Refresh the page** and you should now see row numbers like:
```
1. [Activity details...]
2. [Activity details...]
3. [Activity details...]
```

